Long Description: Cavity not usable or not intended to be used for extended period
Recommended Corrective Actions: No further action required

Long Description: Maintenance: Cavity is known to be bad and is actively being worked on
Recommended Corrective Actions: No further action required

Long Description: Maintenance done but cavity has not been run up for validation
Recommended Corrective Actions: If program permits, set online and verify stability. If stable, leave online. If unstable, comment on/reopen the relevant CATER and set offline

Long Description: Cavity usable but turned off for now
Recommended Corrective Actions: If program permits, set online

Long Description: BSOIC tripped
Recommended Corrective Actions: Communicate the fault to the EOIC and await resolution

Long Description: BSOIC tripped
Recommended Corrective Actions: Communicate the fault to the EOIC and await resolution

Short Description: Not Ready for Beam Chain A
Long Description: PPS: West Global not in Ready for Beam
Recommended Corrective Actions: Communicate the fault to the EOIC and await resolution

Short Description: Not Ready for Beam Chain B
Long Description: PPS: West Global not in Ready for Beam
Recommended Corrective Actions: Communicate the fault to the EOIC and await resolution

Long Description: Hardware Initialization (a.k.a. rack checkout) needs to be run or other LLRF chassis problem. Don't trust current values.
Recommended Corrective Actions: Verify that the rack is not actively being worked on and run Rack Hardware Init and Test > Rack Checkout > Go

Long Description: Hardware Initialization (a.k.a rack checkout) needs to be run or other LLRF chassis problem. Don't trust current values.
Recommended Corrective Actions: Verify that the rack is not actively being worked on and run Rack Hardware Init and Test > Rack Checkout > Go

Long Description: Hardware Initialization (ak.a. rack checkout) currently running. Don't try to use system until this is complete
Recommended Corrective Actions: Wait for fault to clear

Long Description: Hardware Initialization (a.k.a. rack checkout) currently running. Don't try to use system until this is complete
Recommended Corrective Actions: Wait for fault to clear

Long Description: NIRP or other individual SSA interlocks like PPS
Recommended Corrective Actions: If the realtime status is OK (check legend), reset interlocks. If not, contact NIRP system experts.

Long Description: SSA not getting 480V power (isolation switches are likely not closed)
Recommended Corrective Actions: Communicate with the operator(s) to confirm isolation switch status; if the isolation switch is closed, contact AMRF

Long Description: SSA permit to turn on faulted
Recommended Corrective Actions: Run auto setup

Long Description: SSA not on
Recommended Corrective Actions: Run auto setup

Long Description: BCS fault is interrupting LLRF drive (only affects CM01 in practice)
Recommended Corrective Actions: Communicate the fault to the EOIC and await resolution

Long Description: LLRF Frequency is offset from nominal because LLRF has shifted the frequency, or in frequency scan mode
Recommended Corrective Actions: Confirm that this isn't being actively used intentionally and then Rack Larger Range Freq Scan > Shift > Stop

Long Description: LLRF Frequency is offset from nominal because LLRF has shifted the frequency, or in frequency scan mode
Recommended Corrective Actions: Confirm that this isn't being actively used intentionally and then Rack Larger Range Freq Scan > Shift > Stop

Long Description: CM Cryo Summary Interlock (He pressure, He Level, Cryo Heartbeat, and CP Ready) faulted
Recommended Corrective Actions: Check if the summary is OK and if yes, reset interlocks

Long Description: Resonance/ Interlock Link
Recommended Corrective Actions: Contact LLRF team

Long Description: The LLRF digital clock is no longer guranteed to be locked to the accelerator due to the FPGA detecting a temporary loss of externally supplied LO for the onboard clock
Recommended Corrective Actions: Contact LLRF team

Long Description: The LO (local oscillator) signal is used to generate clocks and for RF signal mixing in the RFS and PRC chassis. The system will not work properly if its amplitude is out of range.
Recommended Corrective Actions: CATER and if urgent contact AMRF

Long Description: Interlock trips if the watchdog detects that the IOC is down
Recommended Corrective Actions: Hover over question mark button on screen

Long Description: Beamline Vacuum too high
Recommended Corrective Actions: Contact on call SRF person

Long Description: Beamline Vacuum too high
Recommended Corrective Actions: Contact on call SRF person

Long Description: Coupler manifold vacuum too high
Recommended Corrective Actions: Wait until coupler vacuum is OK and then reset interlocks

Long Description: Coupler manifold vacuum too high
Recommended Corrective Actions: Wait until coupler vacuum is OK and then reset interlocks

Long Description: Temperature sensor on the top of the coupler indicates high temp.
Recommended Corrective Actions: Wait until coupler temperature is OK and then reset interlocks

Long Description: Temperature sensor on the bottom of the coupler indicates high temp.
Recommended Corrective Actions: Wait until coupler temperature is OK and then reset interlocks

Long Description: Temperature sensor on cavity tuner stepper motor out of tolerance.
Recommended Corrective Actions: Write a CATER saying the stepper temperature is out of tolerance and set offline

Long Description: LLRF system detected a cavity quench
Recommended Corrective Actions: Inspect cavity fault waveforms to determine if real or fake. If real, log in SRF log and run auto setup. If fake, reset.

Long Description: Resonance Chassis Summary Fault
Recommended Corrective Actions: Contact LLRF team

Long Description: Latched cavity interlock summary fault
Recommended Corrective Actions: Contact LLRF team

Long Description: Piezo Hardware Fault. Hardware summary status for piezo
Recommended Corrective Actions: Contact LLRF team

Long Description: Stepper Hardware Fault. Hardware summary status for stepper
Recommended Corrective Actions: Check that there isn't standard cavity tuning. If there isn't, Motor Expert > Set Motor Settings

Long Description: Due to changes in the LLRF system, the cavity characterization needs to be run.
Recommended Corrective Actions: Run auto setup

Long Description: This checks that the CW and Pulsed decimations are 255, along with other waveform acquisition settings. Not yet included is the waveform statistics settings in pulsed mode.
Recommended Corrective Actions: Put 255 in all Data Decimation fields in the CW tab

Long Description: Cavity LLRF controller misconfiguration
Recommended Corrective Actions: Contact LLRF team

Long Description: RF is off
Recommended Corrective Actions: Toggle RF State to On

Long Description: Not in SELAP so there is no regulation on amplitude and/or phase
Recommended Corrective Actions: Verify that there is not active cavity ramp up. If there is not, run auto setup

Long Description: RF not ready for beam: mode is not SELAP and/or RF is off
Recommended Corrective Actions: Run auto setup

Long Description: Check Phase: Cavity phase is in an indeterminate state and needs to be measured with the beam before being usable. This fault may appear if something is done to the system that makes 0 phase no longer knowable and ops need to re-gold. This status is set and cleared by experts
Recommended Corrective Actions: If program permits, phase the cavity
Button Path: xterm -iconic -T 'SRF Phase Scan GUI xterm' -e run_matlab.bash —matlab=2020a -r SRF_Phasing

Long Description: Problem with Phase Reference. Cavity phase may not be locked to global RF.
Recommended Corrective Actions: If the program permits and there is RF in the cavity, PRL Tracking > Accept Current Offset. This will put the cavity into CKP and make a re-phasing necessary.

Short Description: PRL phase standard deviation out of tolerance
Long Description: In-use PRL phase STD > 0.02 degrees for 1.3  GHz systems (0.06 degrees for 3.9 GHz systems)
Recommended Corrective Actions: Contact LLRF team

Short Description: PRL phase standard deviation out of tolerance
Long Description: In-use PRL phase STD > 0.02 degrees for 1.3  GHz systems (0.06 degrees for 3.9 GHz systems)
Recommended Corrective Actions: Contact LLRF team

Long Description: Piezo Feedback is not on
Recommended Corrective Actions: Run auto setup

Short Description: Piezo detune and cavity feedback not regulating
Long Description: This alarms if the detune measurement used by the piezo feedback is < -50 Hz or > 50 Hz and the cavity amplitude or phase measurement is out of tolerance.
Recommended Corrective Actions: Contact LLRF team
Generic Short Description for Decoder: Piezo detune and cavity feedback not regulating

Long Description: Piezo Feedback is indicating a problem
Recommended Corrective Actions: Run auto setup

Long Description: Piezo Feedback is indicating a problem
Recommended Corrective Actions: Run auto setup

Long Description: The SSA is unable to output enough power to attain the desired amplitude. Changing the reactive power fraction can help.
Recommended Corrective Actions: Run auto setup. If that fails, try increasing reactive power fraction to no more than 0.5 (will need to press Go). If that fails, CATER

Short Description: Upstream liquid level out of tolerance Alarm
Long Description: Cryomodule liquid level out of tolerance
Recommended Corrective Actions: Call on shift cryo operator

Short Description: Upstream liquid level out of tolerance Warning
Long Description: Cryomodule liquid level out of tolerance
Recommended Corrective Actions: Call on shift cryo operator
Generic Short Description for Decoder: Upstream liquid level out of tolerance

Short Description: Upstream HOM temperature is too high
Long Description: Upstream HOM temperature is too high (could indicate an impending quench)
Recommended Corrective Actions: Turn off RF
Generic Short Description for Decoder: Upstream HOM temperature is too high

Long Description: Downstream HOM temperature too high (could indicate an impending quench)
Recommended Corrective Actions: Turn off RF

Long Description: The amplitude readback is too far away from the desired amplitude
Recommended Corrective Actions: Run auto setup

Long Description: The phase readback is too far away from the desired phase
Recommended Corrective Actions: Check that this isn't being caused by beam feedbacks

Long Description: Quench interlock bypassed
Recommended Corrective Actions: Contact the on call SRF person

Long Description: The feedback maintaining the amplitude is unable to keep the amplitude within tolerance. (Must be checked after RFREADYFORBEAM). Amplitude feedback of measured gradient is too low
Recommended Corrective Actions: Run auto setup

Long Description: The feedback maintaining the phase is unable to keep the phase within tolerance. (Must be checked after RFREADYFORBEAM)
Recommended Corrective Actions: Run auto setup

Long Description: Magnet power supply tripped off
Recommended Corrective Actions: Look at the PS Controller Hardware panel to see what fault tripped off the magnet. CATER and reset

Long Description: Magnet power supply tripped off
Recommended Corrective Actions: Look at the PS Controller Hardware panel to see what fault tripped off the magnet. CATER and reset

Long Description: Magnet power supply tripped off
Recommended Corrective Actions: Look at the PS Controller Hardware panel to see what fault tripped off the magnet. CATER and reset
